        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIG. 2. — Orchidantha virosa Škorničk. & Q.B.Nguyễn, sp. nov.: A, inflorescences (scale in cm above, inches below); B, dissection of flower: entire flower with flower bract and labellum attached, third bract, second bract and prophyll, dorsal sepal and two lateral sepals (scale in cm above, inches below); C, details of petals, anthers and stigma unmanipulated (left), with sepals removed and style, stigma and anthers joined (middle), dorsal view of style and stigma (right) (scale in mm). Photos by Jana Leong-Škorničková." ;
